  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "ブレインドレインは、画面の隅に表示されたリンゴやハートなどの異なるシンボルで構成されたパターンを再現するパズルゲームです。メインのプレイフィールドは、これらのシンボルがランダムに配置されたものです。プレイヤーは、4つのシンボルを囲むフレームを操作します。ボタンを押すと、シンボルがフレームの周りで時計回りに回転します。もちろん、レベルは制限時間内に解決しなければなりません。\n\n難易度が上がると、プレイヤーは「？」ブロックで隠されたシンボルや、自動で回転するシンボル、操作が逆になるなどの特殊効果にも対処しなければなりません。ボーナスレベルをクリアするか、レベルを非常に早くクリアすることで、3つのパワーアップを獲得できます：時計（20秒間時間を停止）、フラッシュ（現在のレベルをスキップ）、クレジット（時間切れ後にもう一度挑戦できる）。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Brain Drain is a puzzle game in which the player has to recreate a pattern, consisting of different symbols like apples or hearts, which is shown in the corner of the screen. The main playing field consists of said symbols, but randomly switched around. The player controls a frame which encloses four of the symbols. When pressing a button, the symbols are rotated clockwise around the frame. Of course the levels have to be solved within a time limit.\n\nIn the higher difficulty levels, the player also has to deal with so-called special effects which occasionally kick in during play, e.g. some symbols get hidden by \"?\" blocks, symbols rotate on their own or the controls are reversed. Three power-ups can be earned by completing bonus levels or finishing a level really fast: clock (stops time for 20 seconds), flash (skips the current level) and credit (gives a second try after time has run out). Clock and flash have to be activated manually; credits is applied automatically. Besides the regular playing mode, there is also the \"Brain Race\" available which involves solving a certain number of levels (depending on the difficulty) as fast as possible.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
